But I've never been to a bookstore before.

256
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,650
Do you want to hear a story?

257
00:19:40,319 --> 00:19:41,990
- Hold this for me. - Okay.

258
00:19:43,549 --> 00:19:45,519
(The Velveteen Rabbit)

259
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:50,690
There was once a velveteen rabbit...

260
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:53,160
who was as chubby as a rabbit should be.

261
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:54,670
The rabbit hopes that someday,

262
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:55,930
he can become...

263
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,329
a real rabbit.

264
00:19:57,940 --> 00:19:59,970
An old leather toy horse told him,

265
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,670
"When a child truly loves you,"

266
00:20:02,940 --> 00:20:04,880
"then you'll become a real rabbit."

267
00:20:05,509 --> 00:20:08,450
So the velveteen rabbit looked forward every day...

268
00:20:08,509 --> 00:20:10,309
to a child that would like him.

269
00:20:12,819 --> 00:20:13,650
One night,

270
00:20:13,819 --> 00:20:14,720
this velveteen rabbit...

271
00:20:14,789 --> 00:20:16,750
was stuffed into the hands of a little boy.

272
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,789
The boy held on to him...

273
00:20:20,190 --> 00:20:21,460
and fell asleep.

274
00:20:24,529 --> 00:20:25,700
The boy's arms...

275
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:27,400
clutched the velveteen rabbit tightly.

276
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:29,329
The rabbit also tucked himself firmly...

277
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,029
under the boy's warm chin.

278
00:20:31,339 --> 00:20:32,670
Every day after that,

279
00:20:32,799 --> 00:20:34,099
they would embrace one another...

280
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:35,640
and fall asleep together.

281
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:37,869
Eventually,

282
00:20:38,039 --> 00:20:39,910
the boy started talking to him.

283
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:44,650
In the boy's eyes,

284
00:20:45,319 --> 00:20:47,279
he was indeed a real rabbit.

285
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:00,529
But...

286
00:21:01,029 --> 00:21:02,930
he'll never find his rabbit now.

287
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:12,579
The end.

288
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:21,519
It stopped raining.

289
00:21:22,089 --> 00:21:23,150
The sun is out.

290
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,990
Let's go.

291
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:32,099
Are you about to run out of battery?

292
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:34,700
Is there anything I can do...

293
00:21:34,769 --> 00:21:36,630
to keep you by my side for much longer?

294
00:21:40,470 --> 00:21:41,670
I want to go home with you.

295
00:21:46,910 --> 00:21:47,710
Let's go home.

296
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:40,000
Everything is still like the first day we met.

297
00:22:42,730 --> 00:22:44,299
But nothing seems the same.

298
00:22:50,339 --> 00:22:52,480
But you're still shining brightly...

299
00:22:53,579 --> 00:22:54,579
like the first time we met.

300
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,019
Hearing you praising me...

301
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:02,549
instead of dissing me...

302
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:05,490
I haven't quite gotten used to it.

303
00:23:09,789 --> 00:23:11,329
I'm so sorry for all the troubles...

304
00:23:12,029 --> 00:23:12,799
I've caused you all this while.

305
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:25,910
Friday.

306
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:31,279
I'll praise you well from now on.

307
00:23:34,049 --> 00:23:34,890
Thank you...

308
00:23:37,150 --> 00:23:38,960
for bringing back 15 years of my life.

309
00:23:41,730 --> 00:23:42,759
You're my friend.

310
00:23:44,190 --> 00:23:45,200
My cure.

311
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,799
You made me open the door to a new world.

312
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:53,470
The days I spent with you were a miracle for me.

313
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:55,339
Thank you.

314
00:23:58,809 --> 00:23:59,640
You know what?

315
00:24:00,309 --> 00:24:03,880
Actually, I didn't cure you.

316
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:07,019
It's what you've longed for...

317
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:08,150
that healed you.

318
00:24:09,049 --> 00:24:12,089
So even if it wasn't me,

319
00:24:12,789 --> 00:24:14,089
anyone...

320
00:24:14,259 --> 00:24:15,589
could've healed you.

321
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:18,630
You're the best master I've ever had.

322
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:21,000
You're the best master in the whole world.

323
00:24:22,299 --> 00:24:24,369
You helped me find my self-worth.

324
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:26,670
You...

325
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:29,440
are also my most precious friend.

326
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:35,450
Thank you, Lu Sen.

